HEADWORD: mantlepiece
<hw>man"tle*piece</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shelf that projects from the
wall above a fireplace; a mantel; <as>as, in England they call a
<ex>mantelpiece</ex> a chimneypiece</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> mantel, mantelpiece, mantle, chimneypiece.</syn>⟦br⟧
